<dl id="n12094e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12094e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12094e"> 94(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> la pleurade</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Souvent la jeune femme pleure en quittant ses parents qui eux aussi versent souvent des larmes, d&apos;o&ugrave; le nom d&apos;<i>Ar oueladen</i> (<mark>la pleurade</mark>). <br><font color="green">[Often the young woman cries when she leaves her parents, who also often shed tears, hence the name d&apos;<i>Ar oueladen</i>, &lsquo;the crying&rsquo;).]</font> <small> Paul-Yves S&eacute;billot, <a name="RDTP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RDTP"><cite title="source">Traditions et coutumes de Basse Bretagne</cite></a> (1904) 356</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
